  "read": "TileLang grouped-D sparse-MLA backward dKV producer with per-route selected-limit metadata. It consumes real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV and packed group ids, recomputes P and scaled dP inside the CTA, then reuses those values across multiple D blocks before final [groups, D] dKV atomics. This avoids the [2, S, topk, H] P/dP HBM slab and reduces the repeated recompute pressure of the older one-D-block recompute-final kernel, at the cost of a larger grouped tile-local accumulator. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer.",
